    "created_at": "2015-08-05T06:03:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-05T06:03:06Z",
    "body": "> If we want to follow the guideline, I think we should do it in API's implementations instead of handling the responsibility to users. But since it is working well, we might just ignore that.\n\nYeah, normally the taskbar button will be created immediately when BrowserWindow is created. I'm fine with this.\n\n> Can you move atom_desktop_window_tree_host_win.\\* to atom/browser/ui/win/?\n\nDone.\n\n> For handling WM_COMMAND message, we can do it in ExecuteWindowsCommand method, instead of hijacking all commands.\n\nWe need the extra information from `w_param` to check the thumbar button click message, and `ExecuteWindowsCommand` Interface only provide the `command_id` message.\n"
